# Wedding planning app — design system v3
## Direction: "Modern romantic" — warmer, bolder

A calm, fast tool with restrained romance. The canvas warms to ivory so white cards lift;
plum reads as confident wine; huge serif moments sit against tight sans UI. Couple names
carry romance in the data, not decoration.

The canonical visual spec is `design/theme-direction.html` (v3). `design/reference.html`
remains for couple-surface component detail (hero, timeline, vendor stepper).

Tokens and fonts are fixed (see bottom). Don't change them without updating the mockup.

---

## Type scale (bold, high-contrast)

The look comes from contrast: huge display moments against small, quiet UI.

Display (Cormorant Garamond 600)
- Page title: 46px, letter-spacing -0.01em
- Stat number (dashboard cards): 54px, color plum
- Budget summary figure: 42px
- Couple names (sidebar, lists, rows): 21–23px serif
- Couple-names hero: `clamp(40px, 6vw, 54px)` — can push toward 64px for more drama
- Countdown number: 64px, color plum
- Wordmark: 25px serif + 9px plum dot

UI (Hanken Grotesk, 400/500)
- Body & rows: 15–16px · Table cells: 14px · Captions/meta: 12–14px
- Eyebrow: 11.5–12px / 500, uppercase, letter-spacing 0.15em, color plum
- Section subhead: 15px / 500

Serif for page titles, stat figures, budget figures, couple-identifying text, and hero
moments. Sans for nav, forms, tables, and all other chrome. The gap between scales is
the design.

---

## Component inventory (exact CSS lives in design/theme-direction.html)

- Topbar: canvas bg, 1px stone bottom border, serif wordmark (25px) with 9px plum dot.
- Pill/status: 12px, dot + label; variants default, sage, clay, rosewood, plum.
- Button: radius 12, 11/22 padding; primary = plum/white, hover plum-deep; secondary =
  surface + stone border.
- Card: surface bg, 1px stone border, radius-lg (16), whisper card-shadow.
- StatCard: padded card with 54px plum serif number + muted label.
- EmptyState: plum-tint wash, 21px serif plum-deep message, no stark white void.
- SectionHeader: uppercase plum eyebrow + hairline stone rule.
- WeddingHero (signature): centered names (display, clamp 40–54) + date (sans muted) +
  64px plum countdown + label, hairline rule beneath, gentle rise-in (respect reduced-motion).
- Timeline: vertical 1px stone spine, nodes (done = sage, current = plum + plum-tint ring),
  tasks as quiet rows with pills.
- Vendor stepper: dot + label + connector; lit steps in plum.
- Budget: serif figures + progress bar (stone-soft track, plum fill) + line items (tabular-nums).
- Planner: sidebar with serif couple names, 3 stat cards, 260px rail + dense tables.

---

## Layout & density
- Couple: single column, max-width 760px, padding 56px 24px 96px, generous rhythm.
- Planner: max-width 1180px, compact rows, 260px rail + table grid.
- Hairline stone separators + whitespace; cards lift via subtle shadow, not heavy gray fills.
- :focus-visible = 2px plum outline. Honor prefers-reduced-motion.

---

## Hard don'ts (these keep it off the generic look)
- No script fonts (except public wedding website templates), floral graphics, gold gradients,
  or blush-pink floods.
- No serif on nav labels, table headers, or form field labels.
- Plum is an accent, never a full-page background flood (plum-tint washes for empty states OK).
- No heavy shadows, glow, or gradients. One whisper card-shadow only. Two sans weights (400/500).

